  m_Name: Pes_Middle_Phalanx_D5_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Middle_Phalanx_D5_R
  partName: Pes Middle Phalanx D5 Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right middle phalanx of the fifth hind digit forms the intermediate skeletal
    segment between the proximal and distal phalanges of the canine toe. This bone
    contributes to flexibility, controlled toe movement, and balanced hindpaw mechanics
    during locomotion. Tendons and ligaments attached to the phalanx allow coordinated
    flexion and extension
  - while supporting traction and stability on different surfaces. The fifth digit
    assists with distributing forces across the hindpaw during walking and running
    activities. Proper structural integrity is important for smooth digital motion
    and efficient locomotion. Injury or abnormalities affecting this phalanx may
    impair toe coordination, reduce stability, and compromise hindpaw function significantly
    in dogs.
